## ✨ CHANGE 1 — Profile Fact Infrastructure

**Goal:** Eliminate factual drift in generated content. When a user states a personal fact in their profile, that fact should never be contradicted in any output.

**Files to modify:** `index.html` (CreatorProfile component + system prompt builder)

### 1a. Add three new profile fields

Add these fields in Phase 2 of the profile (the optional depth section):

```jsx
{/* Personal facts — non-negotiable */}
<div style={{marginBottom: 20}}>
  <label style={labelStyle}>Personal facts VIRL should always get right (optional)</label>
  <textarea
    value={personalFacts}
    onChange={function(e){ setPersonalFacts(e.target.value); }}
    placeholder="Example: I have three sons (ages 4, 7, 10). I'm married to Mike. We live in Indianapolis. I have a golden retriever named Charlie. I run a pilates studio."
    style={Object.assign({}, textareaStyle, {minHeight: 90})}
  />
  <div style={hintStyle}>VIRL will treat these as canonical facts and never contradict them in any output.</div>
</div>

{/* Things to never assume */}
<div style={{marginBottom: 20}}>
  <label style={labelStyle}>Things VIRL should never assume about you (optional)</label>
  <textarea
    value={neverAssume}
    onChange={function(e){ setNeverAssume(e.target.value); }}
    placeholder="Example: Don't assume I have daughters. Don't assume I work from home. Don't assume I'm religious. Don't assume my partner is a husband."
    style={Object.assign({}, textareaStyle, {minHeight: 70})}
  />
  <div style={hintStyle}>If VIRL doesn't know something, it should leave it out — not guess.</div>
</div>

{/* Things to weave in */}
<div style={{marginBottom: 20}}>
  <label style={labelStyle}>Things you'd love VIRL to reference naturally (optional)</label>
  <textarea
    value={loveToReference}
    onChange={function(e){ setLoveToReference(e.target.value); }}
    placeholder="Example: My kids' personalities, our dog Charlie, my morning coffee ritual, our family Sunday tradition."
