Add new state at the top of the CreatorProfile component:
```javascript
var [personalFacts, setPersonalFacts] = useState(profile.personalFacts || "");
var [neverAssume, setNeverAssume] = useState(profile.neverAssume || "");
var [loveToReference, setLoveToReference] = useState(profile.loveToReference || "");
```

Update the `handleSave` function to include these three new fields when persisting to Supabase.

### 1b. Restructure the system prompt

The system prompt must place personal facts at the very top with explicit weight. Refactor the prompt builder so it follows this structure:

```javascript
function buildSystemPrompt(profile, weekContext) {
  var prompt = "";

  // 1. CRITICAL FACTS (top of prompt — non-negotiable)
  if (profile.personalFacts && profile.personalFacts.trim().length > 0) {
    prompt += "## CRITICAL PERSONAL FACTS — NEVER CONTRADICT\n\n";
    prompt += "The following facts about the user are non-negotiable. Every output must be consistent with them. If you cannot incorporate a topic without violating these facts, omit the topic entirely rather than guess:\n\n";
    prompt += profile.personalFacts.trim() + "\n\n";
  }

  if (profile.neverAssume && profile.neverAssume.trim().length > 0) {
    prompt += "## DO NOT ASSUME\n\n";
    prompt += "The user has explicitly stated these are NOT to be assumed:\n\n";
    prompt += profile.neverAssume.trim() + "\n\n";
    prompt += "If you find yourself about to make any of these assumptions, stop and rephrase the content to avoid the assumption entirely.\n\n";
  }

  if (profile.loveToReference && profile.loveToReference.trim().length > 0) {
    prompt += "## NATURAL TOUCHPOINTS\n\n";
    prompt += "The user enjoys when these are referenced naturally (don't force them, but weave them in 1-2 times per week of content where it fits):\n\n";
    prompt += profile.loveToReference.trim() + "\n\n";
  }

  // 2. STANDARD PROFILE CONTEXT (existing logic continues here)
  prompt += "## USER PROFILE\n\n";
  prompt += "Name: " + profile.name + "\n";
  prompt += "Voice: " + profile.voice + "\n";
  prompt += "Audience: " + profile.audience + "\n";
  // ... rest of existing profile fields

  return prompt;
}
```

The KEY structural decision: **CRITICAL FACTS goes first, before everything else.** Models pay disproportionate attention to instructions at the top of the system prompt — using this position for non-negotiable facts dramatically reduces drift.

### 1c. Optional — fact-check pass for high-stakes generation

For plan generation specifically (the highest-stakes output), add a verification pass after generation:

```javascript
async function verifyFacts(plan, profile) {
  if (!profile.personalFacts && !profile.neverAssume) return plan;

  var verifyPrompt = "Review the following 7-day content plan against the user's stated personal facts. Identify any post that contradicts a fact or makes a forbidden assumption. Return a JSON array of {dayIndex: number, issue: string} for any violations found, or an empty array if all posts are compliant.\n\n";
  verifyPrompt += "PERSONAL FACTS: " + profile.personalFacts + "\n";
  verifyPrompt += "DO NOT ASSUME: " + profile.neverAssume + "\n\n";
  verifyPrompt += "PLAN:\n" + JSON.stringify(plan);

  // Call Claude Haiku (cheap, fast)
  var verification = await callClaude("haiku", verifyPrompt);

  // If violations found, regenerate just those posts
  // [implementation: loop through violations, regenerate specific posts with stricter constraints]
  return plan;
}
```

This is optional — ship 1a and 1b first, then add the verification pass if drift continues to be a problem. The first two layers handle 90% of the issue.

### Acceptance test
- Existing user without these fields set → system works exactly as before, no regression
- New user fills in "I have three sons" in personal facts → generated content never references daughters
- User adds "Don't assume I have a husband" to never assume → generated content avoids assumptions about partner
- User fills in "weave in my dog Charlie" to love to reference → roughly 1-2 posts per week reference Charlie naturally
- Profile changes save to Supabase and persist across sessions

