## ✨ CHANGE 3 — Format Diversity in Plan Generation

**Goal:** Eliminate VIRL's video bias. Plans should include a diverse mix of content formats based on the user's profile, industry, and stated preferences.

**Files to modify:** `index.html` (system prompt builder)

### 3a. Add explicit format diversity instructions to the system prompt

After the existing platform context section, add:

```javascript
prompt += "\n## CONTENT FORMAT DIVERSITY\n\n";
prompt += "Generate a diverse mix of content formats across the 7-day plan. Do NOT default all posts to video format. Distribute content across these format types based on the user's selected platform formats and industry context:\n\n";
prompt += "- Video posts (Reels, TikTok videos, YouTube Shorts): high-attention, hook-driven, ideal for entertainment and education\n";
prompt += "- Single image posts (feed photos, Pinterest pins): the caption carries the content, image speaks for itself, ideal for lifestyle/inspiration\n";
prompt += "- Carousel posts (Instagram carousels, LinkedIn document carousels): narrative arc across slides, ideal for educational content, frameworks, lists\n";
prompt += "- Quote graphics / text-on-image: bold typographic posts, minimal caption, ideal for brand voice moments and shareable insights\n";
prompt += "- Stories (Instagram, Facebook): casual, in-the-moment, interactive (polls, questions, tap-throughs), ideal for daily presence and behind-the-scenes\n";
prompt += "- Long-form text (LinkedIn): narrative storytelling, no visual required, ideal for thought leadership and personal essays\n\n";
prompt += "Each post must specify its 'format' field with one of: video, single_image, carousel, quote_graphic, story, long_form_text.\n\n";

// Industry-specific format guidance
var industryFormatGuidance = getFormatGuidance(profile.industry);
if (industryFormatGuidance) {
  prompt += "## FORMAT MIX FOR THIS USER'S INDUSTRY\n\n";
  prompt += industryFormatGuidance + "\n\n";
}
```

### 3b. Industry-specific format mix guidance

